  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Bringing Agenda 2030 to life: Strengthening the role of the Church and voices from the ground</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Agenda 2030 (which includes the Sustainable Development Goals &#x2013; SDGs) includes transformational shifts for how the international community approaches sustainable development. These include leaving no-one behind, protecting the environment, deepening participation and tackling inequality. These correspond closely with key aspects of Catholic Social Teaching: preferential option for the poor, care for our common home and people as artisans of their own destiny &#x2013; all emphasised in Laudato Si&#x2019;. It brings together the cry of the poor and the cry of the earth.</narrative>
  </description>
